caption: During this covid19 time, as a line hating New Yorker, I was pleasantly impressed by the resiliency of this random bar/restaurant that I went to tonight for my uncle's birthday. Covid19 protocol was on deck, temperature check and names were required before entry. The few groups of celebrating gatherers, 2 maybe 3 tops were spaced accordingly and signs were everywhere, even the bathroom reminding us that we were safe in this establishment. Masks on deck with smiles that you knew were there behind the masks, professional staff and service but the music was blah!!! Pretty sure it was an outsourced D.J. that needed a gig, lol! Top shelf drinks are light on tang as well as a pretty good tap on the wallet. I didn't dine here but the atmosphere was welcoming and I shall return! Pro tip, pre-game first and enjoy the space and the welcoming environment to cut loose post covid19!
